OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1779534180
OL,3,CMother who fractured seven-week-old
OL,4,Cdaughter's skull found guilty of murder
OL,6,FA mother who fractured her seven-week-
OL,7,Fold daughter's skull, causing injuries
OL,8,Fwhich contributed to her death more
OL,9,Fthan two years later, has been found
OL,10,Fguilty of her murder.
OL,12,FSarah Ngaba, 32, accepted that she
OL,13,Fcaused "dreadful, life-shortening and
OL,14,Flife-limiting" head injuries to Eliza
OL,15,FNgaba, but denied murder, claiming she
OL,16,Fwas instead guilty of infanticide.
OL,26,@uD@HOUvD@NO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1779534180
OL,3,CMother who fractured seven-week-old
OL,4,Cdaughter's skull found guilty of murder
OL,6,FThe trial heard Ngaba, from Briarwood
OL,7,Fin Telford, was previously convicted
OL,8,Fof causing grievous bodily harm to her
OL,9,Fchild, who was left profoundly
OL,10,Fdisabled by the assault.
OL,12,FNgaba was charged with murder after
OL,13,FEliza died aged two in August 2022
OL,14,Ffrom a respiratory infection, having
OL,15,Fbeen left vulnerable by the assault in
OL,16,FNovember 2019.
OL,18,FEliza's injuries were caused by
OL,19,Fforceful shaking "together with a very
OL,20,Fsignificant impact" to the head,
OL,21,Fcausing a complex skull fracture.
OL,26,@{D@ROU|D@SO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1779534180
OL,3,CMother who fractured seven-week-old
OL,4,Cdaughter's skull found guilty of murder
OL,6,FThe court heard Ngaba took a bath and
OL,7,Fbought a lottery ticket from a shop
OL,8,Fbefore taking Eliza to hospital in a
OL,9,Ftaxi on 13 November 2019.
OL,11,FA witness who saw Eliza on a video
OL,12,Fcall on the morning of the assault
OL,13,F"could see that her body was shaking".
OL,15,FThe man advised Ngaba to take Eliza to
OL,16,Fhospital immediately but the defendant
OL,17,Fsaid she needed to have a bath and did
OL,18,Fnot call an ambulance, the court heard.
OL,26,@uD@AOUuD@eO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1779534180
OL,3,CMother who fractured seven-week-old
OL,4,Cdaughter's skull found guilty of murder
OL,6,FProsecution counsel Jonas Hankin KC
OL,7,Fadded: "Instead, at 8.13am, she rang a
OL,8,Ftaxi company.
OL,10,F"She was told that no taxi was
OL,11,Favailable until 8.50am and that, if
OL,12,Fshe needed to get to hospital sooner,
OL,13,Fshe would have to make alternative
OL,14,Farrangements.
OL,16,F"Despite that she settled for the taxi
OL,17,Fat 8.50am."
OL,26,@oD@HOUrD@AOUxD@AOUyD@KO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1779534180
OL,3,CMother who fractured seven-week-old
OL,4,Cdaughter's skull found guilty of murder
OL,6,FDoorbell footage caught Ngaba leaving
OL,7,Fher flat at 8.40am, and footage from a
OL,8,Flocal supermarket at 8.59am showed her
OL,9,Fbuying a lottery ticket and obtaining
OL,10,Fcashback.
OL,12,FThe taxi driver arrived at 9.05am and
OL,13,Fdescribed the defendant as being very
OL,14,Fcalm and not seeming worried.
OL,16,FOf the defendant's behaviour at the
OL,17,Fhospital, Mr Hankin said: "In triage
OL,18,Fand afterwards, staff described the
OL,19,Fdefendant as annoyed, detached and
OL,20,Fconcerned about housing rather than
OL,21,Fher baby's medical emergency."
OL,26,@yD@[OU}D@^O]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1779534180
OL,3,CMother who fractured seven-week-old
OL,4,Cdaughter's skull found guilty of murder
OL,6,FHe continued: "The prosecution says
OL,7,Fthat this sequence of events is
OL,8,Fimportant.
OL,10,F"Eliza was visibly shaking. The
OL,11,Fdefendant was told to take her to A&E.
OL,12,FAn ambulance was suggested. She didn't
OL,13,Fcall one.
OL,15,F"She chose to bathe and dress first,
OL,16,Faccepted a delayed taxi, went to a
OL,17,Fsupermarket, bought a lottery ticket,
OL,18,Ftravelled calmly to hospital, and did
OL,19,Fnot even rush when she got there.
OL,26,@nD@OOUrD@AOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1779534180
OL,3,CMother who fractured seven-week-old
OL,4,Cdaughter's skull found guilty of murder
OL,6,F"That evidence is difficult to
OL,7,Freconcile with the suggestion that the
OL,8,Fassault on Eliza was the product of an
OL,9,Facute childbirth-caused disturbance of
OL,10,Fmind.
OL,12,F"It is more consistent with a lack of
OL,13,Furgency, with detachment, self-
OL,14,Fconcern, and a failure simply to
OL,15,Fprioritise her daughter's welfare."
OL,17,FTrial judge Mrs Justice Brunner KC
OL,18,Fpaid tribute to Eliza's foster
OL,19,Fparents, who showed "quiet dignity on
OL,20,Fevery day of this trial".
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUwD@cO]{D@UOU|D@XO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1779534180
OL,3,CMother who fractured seven-week-old
OL,4,Cdaughter's skull found guilty of murder
OL,6,FShe added: "It is clear you gave her
OL,7,Fgreat love and care."
OL,9,FShe told Ngaba the sentence she would
OL,10,Fface must be one of life.
OL,12,FNgaba will be sentenced on June 12.
OL,14,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,15,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,16,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,17,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,18,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,19,Fbelow...
